"'''Offshore'''", when used relative to [[hydrocarbon]]s, refers to an [[Petroleum|oil]], [[natural gas]] or [[Natural gas condensate|condensate]] field that is under the sea, or to activities or operations carried out in relation to such a field. There are various [[oil platform|types of platform]] used in the development of offshore oil and gas fields, and [[subsea]] facilities.{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}

Offshore exploration is performed with [[offshore drilling|floating drilling units]].

